Subject: [PATCH 0619/1240] icu: add initial support for ICU unit

the Interrupt Consolidation Unit (ICU) is a unit located in CP-110
that recieves wire interrupts from CP-110 units and converts them
to interrupts messages towards the AP, in AP-806 there is a dedicated
unit that recieves these interrupts and converts them to wired SPI
interrupts on the GIC.

This driver impelements a static mapping of all CP-110 functional and
error interrupts to GIC SPI IDs and AP System Error Interrupts (SEI)
and Ram Error Interrupts (REI).

This driver is temporarily located in u-boot, hence no DT support or
proper integration. It should be moved soon firmware

